<TITLE> Mother of Abdul Awal Mintu dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com)  The mother of former FBCCI president Abdul Awal Mintu died early Saturday at his Gulshan home, due to old age complications. Bodrunessa was 79, Mintu told bdnews24.com. "My mother died around 5 am," he said. "She had been suffering from old age complications for a long time." Bodrunessa left seven sons to mourn her death. She will be buried at Daganbhuiyan in Feni after Asr prayers, the former FBCCI chief said. bdnews24.
